#1 – STRENGTH
A) Deadlift – Build to heavy 5 (H5) for the day @ RPE 8 (2 RIR)

B) Thruster – Build up to a heavy set of 6 (H6)*

* The bar starts on the floor. Do the 1st rep as a squat clean directly into a thruster. Your aim is to go as heavy as you can with good form. Focus on keeping a good balance on your feet, breathing and driving the bar overhead with your hips (not just arms).

C) 12-minute EMOM
1) 8 Thrusters @ 85-90% H6
2) 6 – 12* Bar muscle-ups
3) Rest

* Choose bar muscle-up reps so that you can fight to keep the same reps throughout the EMOM (intent is for this to be a single, unbroken set, each time).

Movement options
Bar muscle-up ? Reduce reps (3 – 5 reps) ? Jumping bar muscle-up

RIR (Reps In Reserve). RIR = How many reps away from failure we want you to go. We will typically work in the 1 – 3 RIR (1 to 3 Reps In Reserve) range to ensure the sets are hard enough to be challenging and for you to make progress.

Notes (A).
– Build up to a heavy set of 5 (H5) @ RPE 8 (2 RIR).
– 5 @ RPE 8 means that this should be a weight you could do for 7 reps in an all-out max effort set.
– You’ll likely find your H5 today in the 80-85%1RM range.

Notes (B).
– Build up to a heavy set of 6 thrusters. Build up as follows: Sets of 6 with lighter weights, drop the reps to 2-4 as the bar gets heavier and then hit your target H6 set ( = aim for a total of 2-3 attempts at H6). Aim to go heavier than last week (H8).

Notes (C).
– Work on your heavy thruster cycling capacity, together with bar muscle-ups. The intent is to move fast with heavy weight on the thruster (remember to BREATHE!) then hit a big set on the bar muscle-ups each round.
